narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I had a great experience this semester. Of course, it entirely depends on having a good relationship with your advisor and a project that excites you. I put a lot of time into research this semester, but found it less stressful than coursework since there aren't any deadlines or exams. The papers and presentations are not a burden, so definitely take the credit if you're doing research anyway.
Independent research under supervision of a professor (and possibly a grad student). You get out what you put in. If you are going to do this, make sure you are interested in the topic of research.
